File: A City of Tshwane Health official stands at the mobile testing unit while waiting to conduct tests for the COVID-19 coronavirus at the Bloed Street Mall in Pretoria Central Business District, on June 11, 2020. PRETORIA - The Tshwane Municipality has shut down three of its buildings - including its headquarters - after staff tested positive for COVID-19. Tshwane House, the municipal facility in Mamelodi West as well as the Silverton fire station will be closed until Friday. The city didn't reveal how many staff members have contracted the virus. It says the buildings will be disinfected over the next four days. Affected employees’ contacts are being traced and their colleagues will be working from home. IN NUMBERS: COVID-19 in SA The country has recorded more than 70,000 cases of the coronavirus - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.